        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 12:14PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 1214 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Grover Hot Springs, or 7 miles east of Carson Pass. This thunderstorm
was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mesa Vista, Woodfords, Grover Hot Springs, Alpine Village,
Markleeville, Hope Valley, Turtle Rock Campground, Junction CA 88 W
And CA 89 N (picketts Junction), Indian Creek Campground, Indian
Creek Reservoir, and Alpine County Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
